data.title: Demitz-Thumitz, Saxony, Germany
data.text:
Demitz-Thumitz, Saxony, Germany is a town located in the eastern part of Germany, near the border with the Czech Republic. The town has a population of around 2,500 people and is known for its beautiful scenery, including the Lusatian Mountains and the Spree River. The town has a long history, dating back to the 13th century, and is home to a number of historical buildings, including the Demitz Castle and the Thumitz Church. The town also has a strong cultural heritage, with a number of festivals and events held throughout the year. The climate in Demitz-Thumitz is temperate, with warm summers and cold winters.
